1
00:00:02,480 --> 00:00:03,600
Danny Pink.

2
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:05,720
Is dead.

3
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:08,480
We're here to get your boyfriend back
from the dead.

4
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:10,880
These are tombs. Water tombs.

5
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:12,720
Why would anyone go to so much trouble?

6
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,920
You're dead.
And this is what's next.

7
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:21,520
A Galyfreyan hard drive.
Time Lord technology.

8
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:26,480
Do you know the key strategic weakness
of the human race?

9
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:28,560
The dead outnumber the living

10
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:29,920
Who are you?

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,720
Oh, you know who I am. I'm Missy.

12
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,480
I couldn't very well keep calling myself

13
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:39,040
the Master, now could I?

14
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:52,640
Stop! You can't kill me!

15
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:53,880
Incorrect.

16
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,920
I'm a target of strategic value.

17
00:00:56,040 --> 00:00:57,800
Alive, I'm a tactical advantage.

18
00:00:57,880 --> 00:01:00,880
Dead, I'm your biggest mistake.
You don't know who I am!

19
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:06,160
You are Clara Oswald. You are human.

20
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:08,080
You are unimportant.

21
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:12,280
Incorrect.

22
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:14,880
You see, that is what
you're supposed to think.

23
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:16,680
That is what everybody thinks.

24
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,680
You are Clara Oswald.

25
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,560
Clara Oswald is a cover story,
a disguise.

26
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:22,200
There is no Clara Oswald.

27
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:26,360
-Identify.
-Oh, don't be so slow,

28
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:28,600
it's embarrassing.
Who could fool you like this?

29
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:31,360
Who could hide right under your nose?

30
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:34,040
Who can change their face
any time they want?

31
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:36,840
(CHUCKLES)

32
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:39,360
You see, I'm not Clara Oswald.

33
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:42,400
Clara Oswald has never existed.

34
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:43,880
Identify.

35
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,400
I'm the Doctor.

36
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,280
Look at them...

37
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,080
My boys!

38
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,400
Cybermen, in broad daylight?

39
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:31,440
You think people won't notice?

40
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:34,160
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING AND LAUGHING)

41
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:39,600
WOMAN: Photos with the big
metal men, one pound!

42
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:43,240
Oh, honey!

43
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,240
There you go!

44
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:51,640
New York, Paris, Rome,
Marrakech, Brisbane, Glasgow.

45
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,760
Everywhere. Anywhere. Me and my boys.

46
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,920
We're going viral.

47
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,480
Would you like me to take a picture?

48
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,880
Sorry, selfies are never
as good, are they,

49
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,640
and you're having
a lovely moment, hang on!

50
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,760
(INDISTINCT)

51
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:06,120
-Nice bow tie.
-Bow ties are cool.

52
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:09,320
Big smiles, and... Now!

53
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:12,560
Move, move, move!

54
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:16,640
Surround target! Hold fast!

55
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,560
Afternoon!

56
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,120
You've picked a lovely day for it.

57
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,680
My, don't you look shiny.

58
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:27,000
Haircut?

59
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,040
-Bit of a trim.
-Might want to do your roots.

60
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:31,040
-The woman!
-SOLDIER: Yes, ma'am.

61
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,320
Kate Stewart. Divorcee, mother of two,

62
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:35,480
keen gardener,
outstanding bridge player.

63
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:39,120
Also chief scientific officer,
Unified Intelligence Task Force,

64
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,720
who currently have you surrounded.

65
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:44,040
Human weaponry is not effective
against Cyber technology.

66
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:47,080
Sorry, you left this behind
on one of your previous attempts.

67
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,160
So, now that I have your attention,

68
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,440
welcome to the only planet
in the universe

69
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:54,120
where we get to say this.

70
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,520
-He's on the payroll.
-Am I?

71
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,000
Well, technically.

72
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,520
-How much?
-Shh!

73
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,800
Any questions?

74
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,560
Back, back, everyone, back!

75
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,400
Oh, my God!

76
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:25,320
-Is it supposed to do that?
-Is that new?

77
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,480
DOCTOR: The sun roof on St Paul's?
Yeah, I'd say that was new!

78
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:31,680
There's going to be mass panic,
everyone in London can see that.

79
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,960
Everyone in London
just clapped and went whee!

80
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,360
Hush, I'm trying to count.

81
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,120
Eighty-seven, I think.

82
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,800
OCD.

83
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:42,480
Ninety-one. Queen of Evil.

84
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:46,200
How could St Paul's be full of
91 Cybermen and nobody noticed?

85
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:49,360
Dimensional engineering
one space folded inside another,

86
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,360
bigger on the inside.

87
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,560
Easy if you're a Time Lord.

88
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:57,600
Mostly deploying south,
a smaller number east.

89
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:01,240
-Yep, but one straight up.
-So, 91 isn't a coincidence?

90
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,520
Of course, it isn't.

91
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,440
KATE: Osgood, 91, explain.

92
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:07,120
Ninety-one areas of significant
population density in the British Isles.

93
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,840
That's one Cyberman
for every city and major town.

94
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:13,040
It's happening everywhere,
all over the world, right now!

95
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,080
Sweet planet, this.

96
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:16,560
I think I might keep it.

97
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:19,760
One Cyberman per city,
what can they hope to accomplish?

98
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,360
Doctor!

99
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,040
(EXPLOSION)

100
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:29,120
-Has it exploded?
-MISSY: More than that.

101
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:32,920
Cybermen don't just blow themselves up
for no good reason, dear.

102
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,080
They're not human.

103
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,400
If it isn't exploding, what's it doing?

104
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,560
Pollinating.

105
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:39,720
Falling like rain
into the cracks of the earth.

106
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,240
SEB: Well, this is a bit exciting!

107
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,520
What's happening?

108
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,600
Well, to cut a long story short,

109
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,240
looks like we might all be going home.

110
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,040
Home?

111
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,720
From the afterlife?

112
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:08,960
Well, when I said afterlife,
I was being a tiny bit poetic.

113
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:11,760
And Nethersphere is just a cool name

114
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,680
we came up with during a spit-ball.

115
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,600
What is this place?

116
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:18,760
Well, you've to think of it
as a data cloud.

117
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:21,200
You know, for storing data.

118
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:24,960
In this case, storage of recently
deceased minds.

119
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,760
-We're in a cloud?
-A sort of cloud, yeah.

120
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,360
And what's happening to it?

121
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:33,280
What happens to any cloud
when it starts to rain.

122
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,720
Are you telling me we're going back?

123
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,840
What, back to our bodies?

124
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:39,640
And the extra good news is,

125
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,520
there's been a bit of an upgrade!

126
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:45,400
MISSY: The dead are coming home, Doctor.

127
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,720
All shiny and new.

128
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:52,880
In 24 hours, the human race,
as you know it, will cease to exist.

129
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,320
What are you doing? Explain!

130
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,200
-Tell me, now!
-Ooh! That was nice.

131
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,440
Let's do it again.

132
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,720
No, no, no, no, I need to talk to her,
I need her awake.

133
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:05,280
Ahh! No!

134
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:08,160
No, stupid!

135
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:10,400
Stupid, no, no!

136
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:18,520
First protocol is implemented,
we're good to go.

137
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,440
You just have to let it take you...

138
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:29,760
What did he say?

139
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,560
He said, guard the graveyards.

140
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:48,000
That's weird. Look at that!

141
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:04,240
How come it's only raining
inside the graveyard?

142
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:37,640
TV REPORTER: We are being told that

143
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,000
these metal men
are known as 'Cybermen,'

144
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,720
but unlike the accounts
we have on file,

145
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,320
they now have the ability to fly.

146
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:48,880
Similar reports are coming in
from all over the world.

147
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,440
Flying Cybermen are here
on a global scale.

148
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:55,680
Ministers are telling us
to remain calm.

149
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:58,560
These Cybermen don't seem
to be attacking us,

150
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,760
at least not in any
conventional fashion.

151
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:04,360
Eye witnesses have reported seeing...

152
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:07,960
(WATER SLOSHING)

153
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,200
(BANGING)

154
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,240
Hello?

155
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,320
(GROWLING)

156
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:18,080
Hello?

157
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,200
(HYDRAULICS WHIRRING)

158
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,600
Whoa!

159
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:47,240
MAN: Put it in position.

160
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,320
Right.

161
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,080
Careful with it.

162
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:07,160
Kate? What's with the hand cuffs?

163
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:11,160
I'm sorry. In the event of
an alien incursion on this scale,

164
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:12,680
protocols are in place.

165
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:15,240
Your co-operation is to be ensured
and your unreliability assumed.

166
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:18,520
-You have a history.
-You don't have a future without me.

167
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,360
Do you think your father
would have done this?

168
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,480
We both know he absolutely would.

169
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:24,560
Who is she?

170
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:26,400
Long story. Where's Clara?

171
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,920
-Clara Oswald, your assistant?
-My friend.

172
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,480
-She was with me in St Paul's.
-The team's still on site.

173
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:33,440
But they've been unable to gain
access to the building.

174
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:35,960
I want her found and brought here.
I need her with me.

175
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,280
Then give the order.

176
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:40,840
As soon as you're on board Boat One,
your word is law. Quite literally.

177
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,800
You got the Tardis out though?

178
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:49,920
Yes. And St Paul's locked down.

179
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,640
Where are we going? Cloudbase?

180
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,680
-You mean the Valiant.
-Cloudbase was Thunderbirds'.

181
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:03,040
Too conspicuous. We need your location
concealed, not advertised.

182
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,520
From now on you're a moving target.

183
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:07,040
Ah, so you're bringing Daddy along too,
that's very sweet.

184
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:08,960
Sir!

185
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:11,600
Don't do that, you look like
you're self-concussing,

186
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,960
which would explain all
of military history,

187
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,640
now I think about it.

188
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:17,920
Colonel Ahmed, sir.
Privilege to meet you.

189
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,880
Love your outfit, Colonel Ahmed,
are you in the Scouts?

190
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,960
Are you a Man Scout?
I didn't know they had those.

191
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:27,400
-It was Captain Scarlet.
-Sorry?

192
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:30,240
-Not Thunderbirds.
-Oh, God, so it was.

193
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:32,960
My confidence is growing every minute.

194
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:34,400
The President is on board.

195
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:38,400
Mind you, me and Sylvia Anderson,
you've never seen a foxtrot like it.

196
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,920
Hang on a second. The President?

197
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:45,080
We don't want Americans
bobbing around the place.

198
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:46,480
They'll only start praying.

199
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:50,000
Not the President of America, sir.
The President of Earth.

200
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:52,160
-There isn't one.
-There is now.

201
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,720
The incursion protocols have been
agreed internationally.

202
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,800
In the event of full-scale invasion,
an Earth president

203
00:11:56,880 --> 00:12:00,440
is inducted immediately, with complete
authority over every nation state.

204
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:02,400
Well, there was only one
practical candidate.

205
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:05,040
Oh, that's your answer for everything,
isn't it? Vote for an idiot.

206
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:07,360
If you say so, Mr President.

207
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,720
So long as you're on this plane,
you are the Commander in Chief

208
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,320
of every army on Earth.

209
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,960
Every world leader
is currently awaiting your instructions.

210
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:17,280
You are the Chief Executive Officer
of the human race.

211
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,320
Any questions?

212
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:22,240
CAPTAIN: This is your Captain speaking,
please prepare for take-off.

213
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:26,480
Well, gentlemen. Where to start?

214
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:29,640
I was born on the planet Gallifrey,
in the constellation of Kasterborous.

215
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,880
I am a Time Lord,
but my Prydonian privileges were revoked

216
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:33,680
when I stole a time
capsule and ran away.

217
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:35,120
Currently piloting a Type 40 Tardis.

218
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,520
I have been married four times,
all deceased.

219
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,680
My children and grandchildren
are missing, and I assume, dead.

220
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:41,320
I have a non-Gallifreyan daughter,
created via genetic transfer.

221
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:44,160
How much more do you need?
I'm the Doctor!

222
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:48,280
This information is not proof.
We require proof.

223
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:51,200
-How about my name?
-Explain.

224
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:53,160
Well, my name isn't Doctor, is it?

225
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:56,600
I don't even really have a doctorate.
Well, Glasgow University,

226
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:59,160
but then I accidentally graduated
in the wrong century, so technically...

227
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,640
This information cannot be confirmed.

228
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:04,880
-You are Clara Oswald.
-Ah! No, I'm not.

229
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:08,200
Your deception is intended
to prolong your life.

230
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:11,160
Your presence has not been ordered.
Correct.

231
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:14,600
-You are Clara Oswald.
-Oh, seriously, this is getting old.

232
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:17,720
Look, there is no Clara Oswald.
I invented her. I made her up.

233
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:20,840
Born 23rd November, 71986.

234
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:23,600
Yeah, I chose that date.
I always liked it.

235
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:27,840
Father, David James Oswald.
Mother, Elena Alison Oswald.

236
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:31,040
Stories. Stories. Stories.
I made them up.

237
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:34,200
Look, ask anybody who knows me.
I'm an incredible liar.

238
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:38,320
Correct.

239
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:44,200
-No order was given.
-Correct.

240
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:46,560
You are not under Cyber control.

241
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,120
Correct.

242
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:03,720
(GASPS)

243
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,800
Why are you still alive?

244
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,960
-You saved me.
-I saved Gallifrey.

245
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,800
Yes, Gallifrey, too, I suppose.

246
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:20,480
There's always collateral damage,
with you and me. It's our Paris.

247
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,960
Gallifrey is lost in another dimension.

248
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:27,120
Yes and no.

249
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:31,200
-Meaning?
-Yes, it's in another dimension.

250
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:34,160
No, it's not lost.

251
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,800
You know where it is?

252
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:40,920
Yep. You know the best part
about knowing?

253
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:45,800
Not telling you.

254
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:49,280
(BEEPING)

255
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:52,760
MAN ON PA: Mr President. sir,
we're ready for you up here.

256
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:57,720
Remember all those years, when all you
wanted to do was to rule the world?

257
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,920
-On my way.
-Thank you, Mr President.

258
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:04,040
Piece of cake.

259
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,720
Oh, erm. It's her little device thingy.

260
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:17,120
I thought there might be
useful information on it.

261
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,440
Who is she?

262
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:20,360
You'd never believe me if I told you.

263
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:23,640
Because I thought she might be
the Master regenerated into female form.

264
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,320
Your childhood friend, responsible
for a number of previous incursions.

265
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,520
That was fairly quick.

266
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:33,040
We do have files on
all our ex-prime ministers.

267
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:35,120
Oh, she wasn't even the worst.

268
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:37,040
Doctor, there's something
nobody's talking about.

269
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,280
Which is?

270
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:40,480
The clouds, caused by
the exploding Cybermen...

271
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:42,880
They haven't dispersed,
they're still there.

272
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:46,880
In fact they have expanded and
are covering almost all the land masses.

273
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:50,880
We're all looking at the graveyards.
Maybe we should be looking up.

274
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,600
What do you think?

275
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:04,160
-All of time and space.
-I'm sorry.

276
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,560
Just something for your bucket list.

277
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:24,480
MAN ON TV: Localised rain in
the cemeteries has resulted in

278
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:29,000
what can only be described as
disturbances to the soil.

279
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:31,320
Extraordinary eye witnesses accounts

280
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,480
are claiming that silver creatures
are climbing from the graves.

281
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,080
These scenes are being
repeated everywhere.

282
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:38,720
Every cemetery. Every mortuary,
every funeral home. Every hospital.

283
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:40,760
The dead are returning to life
as Cybermen.

284
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:44,400
The public are being advised to
stay away from all cemeteries,

285
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,040
(GASPING)

286
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:02,360
(VOICES WHISPERING)

287
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,480
Hello?

288
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:53,240
Hello?

289
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:09,000
We've done heat scans
of some of the cemeteries

290
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:12,360
and in each case, only a handful
of Cybermen have so far emerged

291
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:14,640
but every individual burial site
is active.

292
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:16,520
Active? Hatching.

293
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:19,000
More are coming. Potentially millions.

294
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:21,840
So the rain caused all that
in just a few hours?

295
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:26,000
It wasn't rain, Man Scout!
It was pollen. Cyber-pollen.

296
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:28,400
Every tiny particle of a Cyberman

297
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:30,600
contains the plans
to make another Cyberman.

298
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:33,680
All it has to do is make a contact
with compatible,

299
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:36,440
living organic matter,
and bang, full conversion.

300
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:41,200
But if they've learned
how to convert the dead...

301
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:45,120
That's what she was doing!

302
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:48,280
That's what 3W was for!

303
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:52,360
She creates an all new paranoia
among the super-rich about dying,

304
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:55,800
she exploits the wealth
and the mortal remains

305
00:18:55,880 --> 00:19:00,960
of selected idiots, so she can create
a whole new race of Cybermen.

306
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,240
Cybermen who can recruit corpses.

307
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:07,920
Throw away your guns, Man Scout,
it's all over.

308
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:12,440
How can you win a war against an enemy
that can weaponise the dead?

309
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,800
AHMED: They're not attacking apart from
isolated incidents,

310
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,280
they're just wandering about.

311
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:54,280
DOCTOR: They're new-borns.
Give them time.

312
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:56,400
Why were you there this morning,
why were you already attacking?

313
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:59,440
Been investigating 3W for a while.
Then we got a tip off.

314
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:01,160
From a woman with a Scottish accent.

315
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:03,880
Can't play to the gallery,
unless there's a gallery. And here I am.

316
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:07,360
Dead bodies don't have minds,
of course.

317
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:11,000
But she's been upgrading dying minds
to a hard drive for a long time.

318
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:12,840
So, she upgrades the hardware,

319
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:14,360
then she updates the software.

320
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:16,360
What do you mean,
a long time? How long?

321
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:18,960
She must have a Tardis somewhere.
So, as long as she likes,

322
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:21,840
-the past and future...
-How long, Doctor?

323
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:26,000
How long has the human race
had a concept of an afterlife?

324
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:28,480
Turns out the afterlife is real.

325
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:30,800
And it's emptying.

326
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:33,600
Every graveyard on planet Earth

327
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,040
is about to burst its banks.

328
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,720
(MISSY SINGING)

329
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:49,640
Hey, Missy, you're so fine,
you're so fine,

330
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,720
you blow my mind.
Hey, Missy!

331
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,200
Hey... (LAUGHS)

332
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:54,280
Excuse me.

333
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:56,280
Hi.

334
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,880
Can I tell you something
really important?

335
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,000
What?

336
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:03,680
I have to whisper it.

337
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:08,000
It's, like, so important
to everyone on this plane,

338
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:10,400
that you'll get in trouble
if you don't listen.

339
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:12,120
If it was that important,
why would you tell us?

340
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,800
Well, look at me, I'm bananas.

341
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:16,320
Come on, just a wee bit closer.

342
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:20,000
Just a little closer, you know,
the Doctor will be really impressed

343
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,080
if you learn my secrets.

344
00:21:31,760 --> 00:21:34,000
Well, you can come a bit closer
than that. Stop mucking about.

345
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:35,200
Don't be shy.

346
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:36,960
You don't smell half as bad
as you think you do.

347
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:42,360
There are two armed men
directly behind you.

348
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:43,560
Yeah, yeah, yeah!

349
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,360
If you've got something to say,
just say it.

350
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,440
(CLEARING THROAT)

351
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:53,960
(WHISPERS) I'm going to kill you
in a minute.

352
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:59,480
I'm not even kidding,

353
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:02,120
you're gonna be as dead
as a fish on a slab any second now,

354
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:04,080
all floppy and making smells.

355
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:06,040
But don't tell the boys,

356
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:08,600
this is our secret girl plan.

357
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:11,400
Why would you bother killing me?
I'm not even important.

358
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:15,160
Oh, silly! Why does one pop a balloon?

359
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:17,240
Because you're pretty.

360
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,800
You should have a bit
more confidence in yourself.

361
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:22,280
Okay.

362
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:24,160
Sorry, I've got work to do.

363
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:26,320
All right fine, you get on.

364
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:28,040
You get that finished.

365
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:30,720
Would a countdown help you
focus at all?

366
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:32,240
-No, that's okay.
-Ten.

367
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:33,480
Don't be scared yet, 'cause I'm still

368
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:34,600
- in double figures.
-I'm not scared.

369
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:36,960
Nine. Of course you're not,
because you know you're dying anyway.

370
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:40,480
Eight. Human beings are born dying.
Your life spans are hilarious.

371
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:41,880
Please be quiet.

372
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:45,120
Seven. You know,
from the minute you slop out

373
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:47,880
you're rotting, decaying.

374
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:49,800
The stench of you. Oof!

375
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,640
I'm never going to get
this place clean.

376
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:53,400
-Three!
-Three?

377
00:22:53,560 --> 00:22:55,440
I'm accelerating for dramatic effect.

378
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:56,880
(GASPS) Oh!

379
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,880
What's that in your pocket?

380
00:23:01,160 --> 00:23:02,800
There's nothing in my...

381
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:05,800
Oh, my giddy aunt.

382
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,640
The quiet ones are the worst.

383
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,720
Well, those aren't mine!

384
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:18,560
Then they must be mine!

385
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:22,000
(GRUNTS)

386
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:24,600
Say something nice.

387
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:27,280
Missy! The Master!

388
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:30,960
Whatever you call yourself. I promise,
I'm much more useful to you alive.

389
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,920
Oh, yeah, that's true.
That's definitely true,

390
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,120
that is a good point, well made...

391
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:38,760
I'm proud of you, sister.
But did I mention?

392
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,520
Bananas!

393
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:42,440
Pop!

394
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,560
Ah!

395
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:48,520
Thanks for being yummy.

396
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:07,280
Mr President, you need
to get back in your seat.

397
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:09,400
I don't like being President,
people keep saluting.

398
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:11,080
I'm never going to salute back.

399
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:13,760
You know, that was always
my Dad's big ambition,

400
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:16,280
to get you to salute him, just once.

401
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:19,360
He should've asked.

402
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:25,720
-Doctor, what are you looking at?
-The clouds.

403
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:28,920
Still there, so what else
have they got?

404
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:31,760
Oh, dear Lord!

405
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:33,480
There's a Cyberman
out there on the fuselage.

406
00:24:33,920 --> 00:24:35,800
On the plus side, it's not turbulence.

407
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,760
She's out!

408
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:40,680
Who let her out?

409
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:43,200
What's it doing? Where did it go?

410
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:45,920
What can one Cyberman do to a plane?

411
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:10,000
Oh, she was really scared,
it was classic!

412
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:15,320
Have you got any more friends
I can play with?

413
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,400
(CYBERMAN MUMBLING)

414
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,720
Are you the one that brought me here?

415
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:43,280
Affirmative.

416
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:45,920
-So you know who I am, right?
-You are not the Doctor.

417
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:49,280
Of course, I'm not the Doctor,
I was lying to stay alive.

418
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:51,040
But how do I know so much about him?

419
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:53,360
-You are his associate.
-I'm not.

420
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:55,280
I'm not his associate,

421
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,320
I'm his best friend.

422
00:25:57,720 --> 00:26:00,040
Right now, his best friend,
anywhere in the universe.

423
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:01,480
Have you got any sort of
Cyber-Internet in there,

424
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:03,800
because really, you should look it up.

425
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:06,200
Look up what happens to you
if you harm me.

426
00:26:06,280 --> 00:26:08,400
-Where is the Doctor?
-(CHUCKLES)

427
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:11,480
What, you think I'd give up the Doctor?
Don't be daft.

428
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:15,440
I would never, ever,
give up the Doctor.

429
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:17,520
Because he is my best friend, too.

430
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:20,040
He is closest person to me
in this whole world.

431
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,920
He's the man I will always forgive,

432
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:25,120
always trust, the one man
I would never, ever lie to...

433
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:52,840
Danny?

434
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:56,200
Danny Pink is dead.

435
00:26:58,120 --> 00:26:59,360
Help me.

436
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:01,920
Oh, my God!

437
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:04,160
Danny!

438
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:10,960
-Help me.
-Danny!

439
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,240
I'm so sorry.

440
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:16,320
Help me! I need you
to do something for me.

441
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:18,720
I can't do it myself.

442
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,040
What is that?

443
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:28,680
It's an inhibitor.

444
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:30,560
It's not activated.

445
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:32,240
I need you to switch it on.

446
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:34,240
What does it inhibit?

447
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:37,360
Emotion. It deletes emotions.

448
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:41,000
Please, I don't want to feel like this.

449
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:51,120
-There's more than one.
-KATE: What?

450
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,840
They're all over the plane,
they're pulling it apart!

451
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:57,320
Whoa!

452
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,760
-Ask me.
-Shut up!

453
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:04,760
Ask me! Go on, you know you want to.

454
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:06,800
You want to know what my plan is.

455
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:08,400
You'll be surprised.

456
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:10,640
I got a gift for you.

457
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:13,800
You know, I've been
up and down your time line,

458
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:17,880
meeting all those silly people
who die to keep you alive.

459
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:19,520
You know what I worked out?

460
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:22,200
-What you really need?
-For what?

461
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:24,040
To know that you're just like me.

462
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:25,880
-(PHONE RINGING)
-Oh!

463
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:28,000
And now it begins.

464
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:33,640
Doctor, I do believe you're on call.

465
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:36,280
Miss Oswald expects.

466
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:40,400
Who else? But the girl
who's got your number.

467
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:42,600
Whoops!

468
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:47,880
It was you!

469
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:53,280
-Ah! Hello!
-Where did you get this number?

470
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:55,000
The woman in the shop wrote it down,

471
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,120
it's a helpline, isn't it?

472
00:28:56,320 --> 00:28:58,280
Computer helpline, love!

473
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:00,320
That's the one.

474
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:03,320
Best helpline in the universe.

475
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:07,200
You put us together.

476
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:09,000
I kept you together.

477
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:12,120
-Who put that advert in the paper?
-Who gave you my number?

478
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:14,200
The woman, the woman in the shop.

479
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:17,240
And there's a woman out there
who is very keen that we stay together.

480
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:20,680
-Why?
-Because she's perfect, innt?

481
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:24,640
The control freak and the man
who should never be controlled.

482
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:28,360
You'd go to hell, if she asked.
And she would.

483
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:30,680
The phone's ringing, Doctor.
Can't you hear that?

484
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:33,960
Now, that is the sound
of your chain being yanked.

485
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:35,760
Heel, Doctor!

486
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:39,880
Help me Doctor!

487
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:42,360
Help me, help me, Doctor!

488
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:44,280
-Clara?
-Doctor?

489
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,400
-With Danny.
-Danny's dead, Clara.

490
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:50,400
Not yet. Not quite.

491
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:52,160
But he wants to be.

492
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,800
Clara?

493
00:29:58,040 --> 00:29:59,200
Clara?

494
00:30:02,280 --> 00:30:03,840
He's a Cyberman.

495
00:30:04,560 --> 00:30:06,200
Doctor, Danny's a Cyberman.

496
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:10,600
And he's crying.
Doctor, he feels it, he's crying.

497
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:19,320
Message to Geneva.
Tell them Boat One is going down,

498
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:21,240
we don't anticipate survivors.

499
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:32,760
Clara, don't do it, just don't do it!

500
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:36,280
It's in his chest,
he says it's an inhibitor.

501
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:37,760
It can delete emotion, or something...

502
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,440
I know what it does.

503
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:42,320
If you turn it on,
he'll become a Cyberman.

504
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,640
-He's already a Cyberman.
-Not yet, he isn't.

505
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:48,960
He's hurting because I hurt him.
And he wants it to stop.

506
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:50,920
Stop the pain, and he'll kill you!

507
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:55,960
Look, are you going to help me
because I can't do this alone?

508
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:58,280
I am not going to help
you commit suicide.

509
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:00,920
Look the Tardis can home in
on this call, right?

510
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:03,960
Either you help me,
or you leave me alone.

511
00:31:05,360 --> 00:31:06,880
Clara, no!

512
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:14,320
There's a lot of switches
round the edge.

513
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,360
I'm just going to try pressing them all.

514
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:17,840
Okay.

515
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:29,000
I am so sorry.

516
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:31,280
Yeah.

517
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:36,640
Doctor! The Cybermen are in,
the plane's going down.

518
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:41,120
Oh, great. It's the daughter one.
Do you like her? I like her.

519
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:51,680
Why did you do that?
You didn't have to do that!

520
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:59,160
Oh, don't be so selfish.
I'm going to miss her, too.

521
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:03,120
In fact, you know what,
just for that, I'm leaving.

522
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:08,080
Boys, blow up this plane
and, I don't know, Belgium, yeah?

523
00:32:08,600 --> 00:32:10,360
(PANTING)

524
00:32:10,680 --> 00:32:15,200
Kill some Belgians, might as well,
they're not even French. Bye.

525
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:29,680
(SCREAMING)

526
00:32:33,080 --> 00:32:35,400
Well, that's very boring!

527
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:39,840
He's just going to squish.

528
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:45,760
What kind of a way is that to die?
That man has no finesse, none.

529
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,240
It's quite dramatic.

530
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:51,160
You're an Al interface,
kindly delete your opinions. Thank you.

531
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:57,800
What's he doing? Is he...

532
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:06,600
Oh, no! No, no, now that's...

533
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:20,840
Oh! Permission to squee!

534
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:51,640
Two more to go.
Does it feel any different?

535
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,360
-(TARDIS WHOOSHING)
-No.

536
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:57,080
-Are you sure?
-Yeah.

537
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:01,440
Clara, don't.

538
00:34:04,920 --> 00:34:06,000
Help me.

539
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:09,040
If you do what you're trying to do,
if you succeed, he will snap you.

540
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:10,280
-No.
-And then he will step

541
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:12,520
over your broken body, and break
another and another and another.

542
00:34:12,640 --> 00:34:14,760
-He will never stop.
-I will not harm her.

543
00:34:27,640 --> 00:34:30,280
P.E PE.

544
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:32,320
Sir.

545
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:40,680
I had a friend once.

546
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:42,920
We ran together, when I was little.

547
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:44,800
And I thought we were the same.

548
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:48,400
But when we grew up, we weren't.

549
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:52,600
Now, she is trying
to tear the world apart,

550
00:34:52,680 --> 00:34:55,880
and I can't run fast enough
to hold it together. The difference...

551
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:02,600
...is this. Pain is a gift.

552
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:08,320
Without the capacity for pain,
we can't feel the hurt we inflict.

553
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:12,440
Are you telling me seriously,
for real that you can?

554
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:15,880
-Of course I can.
-Then, shame on you, Doctor.

555
00:35:15,960 --> 00:35:17,160
Yes.

556
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,000
Oh, yes.

557
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:30,600
Danny. Danny, I need you to tell me,

558
00:35:30,680 --> 00:35:33,760
what are the clouds going to do,
what is the plan?

559
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:37,400
-How would I know?
-You're part of a hive mind now,

560
00:35:37,480 --> 00:35:41,840
presumably that's how you found Clara.
Just look.

561
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:44,840
-Can't see much.
-Look harder.

562
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:50,080
Clara, watch this.
This is who the Doctor is.

563
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:53,920
Watch the blood-soaked
old general in action.

564
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:57,960
I can't see properly, sir,
because this needs activating.

565
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:02,880
If you want to know what's coming,
you have to switch it on.

566
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:08,600
And didn't all of those beautiful
speeches just disappear

567
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:10,960
in the face of a tactical advantage?

568
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,360
Sir?

569
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:28,200
Ahh. I need to know.

570
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:33,480
I need to know.

571
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:37,000
Yes. Yes, you do.

572
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:41,360
Give me the screwdriver.

573
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:44,400
-No.
-Just do it, Doctor.

574
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,840
Do as you are told.

575
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:00,000
Typical officer.

576
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:02,400
Got to keep those hands clean.

577
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:14,280
-Just point and think, yeah?
-Yes.

578
00:37:16,920 --> 00:37:18,000
Okay.

579
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:27,520
I wasn't very good at it.
But I did love you.

580
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:30,640
I loved you, too.

581
00:37:34,160 --> 00:37:35,840
I'm never going to say that again.

582
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:38,320
Me neither.

583
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:44,960
-Ready?
-Yeah.

584
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:49,720
It feels like I'm killing you.

585
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:52,680
I'm already dead.

586
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,680
You're here this time at least.

587
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:58,160
Goodbye, Danny.

588
00:38:00,160 --> 00:38:01,560
Goodbye, Clara.

589
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:06,800
(BUZZING)

590
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:12,600
Oh...

591
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:16,760
Ah, no, no, no. Wait, he's activating.
Clara, step away! No, don't!

592
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:22,960
Danny, if you can hear me,
if you're still there...

593
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:24,840
What are the clouds going to do?

594
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:28,880
The rain will fall again.
All humanity will die.

595
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:32,920
-And rise again as Cybermen?
-Correct.

596
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:36,920
-How do we stop it?
-We cannot be stopped.

597
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:44,360
Oh, that was brilliant!

598
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:48,800
Well, love the telly here,
but did you see that?

599
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:53,720
Oh, Clara, you poor thing,
you must feel like death.

600
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:55,560
Let me pop away the pain.

601
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:57,520
Don't you dare! Don't you
even think about it!

602
00:38:57,600 --> 00:39:00,240
I'm sorry, hon. I'm just getting
a bit carried away.

603
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:02,520
It's your friends, they're so moreish.

604
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:06,440
Hmm. Oh, stop looking all cross-pants.

605
00:39:07,720 --> 00:39:11,600
I'm here to give you your gift.
Could you at least try and be excited?

606
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:13,040
What gift?

607
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:16,880
Cyberdears!

608
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:20,960
Look at mummy! Raise your arms.

609
00:39:21,920 --> 00:39:24,400
Lower your arms. Raise your right.

610
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:27,400
Lower your right. Turn on the spot.

611
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:33,640
There are exits at the front
and rear of the aircraft.

612
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:37,360
Please follow the lights up the aisle.

613
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:41,160
You see, Doctor? The power
to slaughter whole worlds at a time,

614
00:39:41,240 --> 00:39:43,320
then make them do a safety briefing.

615
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:48,720
Everyone who ever lived, man, woman,
and child is now at my command.

616
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:51,840
An indestructible army
to rage across the universe.

617
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:54,120
The more they kill,
the more they recruit.

618
00:39:56,440 --> 00:39:57,760
Happy birthday.

619
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:02,880
Oh, you didn't know, did you?

620
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:07,200
It's lucky one of us
remembers these things.

621
00:40:08,240 --> 00:40:09,600
Happy birthday,

622
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:13,800
# Mr President.

623
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:19,960
Doctor.

624
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:21,560
MISSY: Tiny bit pleased?

625
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:27,840
Oh, go on, crack a smile.

626
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:29,720
I want to see if your eyebrows drop off.

627
00:40:29,880 --> 00:40:31,280
All of this...

628
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:33,760
All of it, just to give me an army?

629
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,920
MISSY: Well, I don't need one, do I?

630
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:38,600
Armies are for people
who think they're right.

631
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:41,400
Nobody thinks they're righter than you.

632
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:44,240
Give a good man fire-power,

633
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,080
and he'll never run out
of people to kill.

634
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:47,400
I don't want an army!

635
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:50,200
Well, that's the trouble! Yes, you do!

636
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:52,120
You've always wanted one!

637
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:54,360
All those people suffering
in the Dalek camps?

638
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:58,480
Now you can save them. All those bad
guys winning all the wars?

639
00:40:58,600 --> 00:41:00,480
Go and get the good guys back.

640
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:02,680
-Nobody can have that power.
-You will,

641
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,360
because you don't have a choice.
There's only

642
00:41:04,440 --> 00:41:07,480
one way you can stop these clouds
from opening up

643
00:41:07,560 --> 00:41:10,360
and killing all your
little pets down here.

644
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:13,400
Conquer the universe, Mr President.

645
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:16,480
Show a bad girl how it's done.

646
00:41:17,440 --> 00:41:18,920
Why are you doing this?

647
00:41:19,040 --> 00:41:22,040
I need you to know
we're not so different.

648
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:26,920
I need my friend back.

649
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:31,320
Every battle, every war, every invasion,

650
00:41:32,040 --> 00:41:34,320
from now on, you decide the outcome.

651
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:36,720
What's the matter, Mr President?

652
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:40,160
Don't you trust yourself?

653
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:43,800
DOCTOR: T7ell me.

654
00:41:44,760 --> 00:41:46,160
Am I good man?

655
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:48,160
Sir!

656
00:41:56,640 --> 00:41:59,720
DALEK: I see into your soul, Doctor.

657
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:04,160
I see hatred!

658
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:07,800
I'm not a hero!

659
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:11,320
DALEK: You are a good Dalek!

660
00:42:12,040 --> 00:42:13,760
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

661
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:21,080
Thank you. Thank you, so much.

662
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:26,280
I really didn't know. I wasn't sure.
You lose sight sometimes.

663
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:27,800
Thank you.

664
00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:31,760
I am not a good man.

665
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:36,800
And I'm not a bad man.

666
00:42:37,520 --> 00:42:39,320
I'm not a hero.

667
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:44,440
I'm definitely not a president.
And, no, I'm not an officer.

668
00:42:44,760 --> 00:42:46,160
You know what I am?

669
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:50,160
I am an idiot,

670
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:53,760
with a box and a screwdriver.

671
00:42:54,480 --> 00:42:58,520
Passing through, helping out. Learning.

672
00:42:58,840 --> 00:43:01,000
I don't need an army, I never have.
'Cause I've got them.

673
00:43:01,480 --> 00:43:03,120
Always them.

674
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:06,000
Because, love, it's not an emotion.

675
00:43:07,560 --> 00:43:08,720
Love is a promise,

676
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:14,440
and he will never hurt her.

677
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:16,480
P.E., catch!

678
00:43:20,040 --> 00:43:21,640
You didn't notice, did you?

679
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:23,600
While you were doing
all your silly orders,

680
00:43:23,720 --> 00:43:25,040
while you were showing off,

681
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:26,480
the one soldier not obeying.

682
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:28,400
No, that's wrong. That's impossible.

683
00:43:30,360 --> 00:43:32,080
The rain will not fall.

684
00:43:32,440 --> 00:43:34,120
Oh? Why won't it?

685
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:35,600
The clouds will burn.

686
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:37,880
-And who'll burn them?
-I will burn them.

687
00:43:38,200 --> 00:43:39,200
How?

688
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:41,160
I will burn.

689
00:43:41,480 --> 00:43:44,960
One burning Cyberman is hardly
going to save the planet.

690
00:43:46,480 --> 00:43:47,480
Correct.

691
00:43:52,520 --> 00:43:53,640
Attention!

692
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:57,480
This is not a good day.

693
00:43:57,840 --> 00:43:59,880
This is Earth's darkest hour.

694
00:44:00,760 --> 00:44:03,000
And look at you miserable lot.

695
00:44:03,800 --> 00:44:07,360
We are the fallen.
But today we shall rise.

696
00:44:07,600 --> 00:44:09,400
The army of the dead,

697
00:44:09,720 --> 00:44:11,640
will save the land of the living.

698
00:44:11,960 --> 00:44:14,080
This is not the order of a general.

699
00:44:15,520 --> 00:44:17,840
-Nor the whim of a lunatic...
-Excuse me!

700
00:44:18,520 --> 00:44:19,840
This is a promise!

701
00:44:21,320 --> 00:44:23,080
The promise of a soldier!

702
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:28,240
You will sleep safe tonight.

703
00:44:30,840 --> 00:44:32,480
-(BEEPING)
-(STEAM HISSING)

704
00:44:48,840 --> 00:44:49,840
(EXPLOSION)

705
00:45:15,440 --> 00:45:16,440
Well.

706
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:20,280
-The clouds have all gone.
-Yes.

707
00:45:21,120 --> 00:45:23,640
Burned up, totally burned.

708
00:45:24,560 --> 00:45:26,160
Burned to nothing.

709
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:32,240
Sorry.

710
00:45:32,600 --> 00:45:35,800
10-0-11-0-0 by 0-2.

711
00:45:36,040 --> 00:45:37,560
DOCTOR: What did you say?

712
00:45:37,960 --> 00:45:40,440
The current co-ordinates of Gallifrey.

713
00:45:40,840 --> 00:45:43,880
It's returned to its original location.
Didn't you ever think to look?

714
00:45:43,960 --> 00:45:44,960
You are lying.

715
00:45:46,400 --> 00:45:49,400
We can go together. Just you and me,
just like the old days.

716
00:45:49,880 --> 00:45:51,120
You'll be clapped in irons.

717
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:53,000
If you like.

718
00:45:53,640 --> 00:45:56,600
Doctor, I'm assuming you'll
remember those co-ordinates?

719
00:45:57,560 --> 00:45:59,280
No. Don't you dare, I won't let you.

720
00:45:59,760 --> 00:46:01,080
Old friend, is she?

721
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:04,600
If you've ever let this creature live,

722
00:46:04,720 --> 00:46:06,440
everything that happened today
is on you.

723
00:46:06,960 --> 00:46:08,640
All of it, on you.

724
00:46:10,720 --> 00:46:12,120
And you are not
gonna let her live again.

725
00:46:12,200 --> 00:46:13,200
Clara,

726
00:46:14,240 --> 00:46:17,160
all I'm doing,
is not letting you kill her.

727
00:46:18,160 --> 00:46:20,080
I never said I was letting her live.

728
00:46:22,760 --> 00:46:23,760
Really?

729
00:46:23,880 --> 00:46:28,720
If it's the only thing
that will stop you, yes.

730
00:46:40,320 --> 00:46:41,320
Seriously?

731
00:46:43,720 --> 00:46:46,480
Oh, Doctor.

732
00:46:48,360 --> 00:46:49,760
To save her soul?

733
00:46:53,280 --> 00:46:54,280
(CHUCKLES)

734
00:46:56,680 --> 00:46:58,720
But who, my dear, will save yours?

735
00:47:01,600 --> 00:47:03,080
Say something nice.

736
00:47:07,600 --> 00:47:08,600
(SIGHING)

737
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:10,200
Please.

738
00:47:12,840 --> 00:47:14,080
You win.

739
00:47:15,880 --> 00:47:16,880
I know.

740
00:47:19,120 --> 00:47:20,960
-(BEEPING)
-(ZAPPING)

741
00:47:32,880 --> 00:47:33,960
Doctor!

742
00:47:41,760 --> 00:47:42,800
DOCTOR: Kate!

743
00:47:43,880 --> 00:47:45,280
She's breathing.

744
00:47:45,840 --> 00:47:47,560
She's alive! She can't be here!

745
00:47:47,680 --> 00:47:48,880
She is.

746
00:47:48,960 --> 00:47:50,560
She fell out of a plane.

747
00:47:53,760 --> 00:47:55,080
The Cyberman...

748
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:57,440
Must have caught her.

749
00:47:59,640 --> 00:48:02,360
Doctor. She's talking about her dad!

750
00:48:07,200 --> 00:48:08,480
Of course!

751
00:48:08,560 --> 00:48:10,920
The Earth's darkest hour, and mine.

752
00:48:12,160 --> 00:48:13,840
Where else would you be?

753
00:48:29,840 --> 00:48:31,080
Thank you.

754
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:39,440
(SIRENS BLARING IN DISTANCE)

755
00:48:46,960 --> 00:48:48,440
DANNY: Clara.

756
00:48:49,840 --> 00:48:51,240
Clara.

757
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:54,600
Danny.

758
00:48:56,680 --> 00:48:57,720
Danny?

759
00:48:58,040 --> 00:48:59,920
Is that you?

760
00:49:00,600 --> 00:49:02,240
Please say it's you.

761
00:49:08,280 --> 00:49:09,320
DANNY: Clara.

762
00:49:09,440 --> 00:49:11,040
The Doctor told me about the bracelet.

763
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:13,240
How it can let Missy travel
from one world to the other.

764
00:49:13,560 --> 00:49:15,320
DANNY: This place is dying now.

765
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:18,320
Yes, but the bracelet
can bring you home.

766
00:49:18,520 --> 00:49:20,360
There's only enough power for one trip.

767
00:49:20,520 --> 00:49:23,080
Then come on, hurry up!

768
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:24,600
Just one trip.

769
00:49:24,960 --> 00:49:26,400
One trip, one person.

770
00:49:31,440 --> 00:49:32,960
CLARA: Danny!

771
00:49:41,640 --> 00:49:43,480
You need to find his parents.

772
00:49:44,840 --> 00:49:46,440
He died a long time ago.

773
00:49:47,880 --> 00:49:49,080
(GASPING)

774
00:49:51,640 --> 00:49:53,160
I'm sorry, Clara.

775
00:49:53,320 --> 00:49:54,800
(VOICE BREAKING) I truly am.

776
00:49:56,360 --> 00:49:58,440
I had... I had promises to keep.

777
00:50:00,280 --> 00:50:01,480
(CRACKLING)

778
00:50:08,880 --> 00:50:10,240
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

779
00:50:10,960 --> 00:50:12,400
(DOOR CHIMES JANGLING)

780
00:50:16,480 --> 00:50:18,680
-Hey. I got your message.
-Hey.

781
00:50:18,800 --> 00:50:20,400
-Two weeks late.
-Not bad.

782
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:21,480
Improving.

783
00:50:23,440 --> 00:50:25,920
- I see you've got news for me.
-News?

784
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:27,000
He figured it out then.

785
00:50:28,240 --> 00:50:30,600
P.E., figured out there was a way home.

786
00:50:31,360 --> 00:50:32,760
Yeah. Yeah, he did.

787
00:50:33,040 --> 00:50:34,680
Oh, good old P.E.

788
00:50:35,080 --> 00:50:36,560
He'll make a maths teacher yet.

789
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:38,920
Listen, Doctor. There's...

790
00:50:39,760 --> 00:50:42,640
There's something that
I have to tell you. And, um,

791
00:50:44,640 --> 00:50:45,800
it's not a good news, so...

792
00:50:45,920 --> 00:50:47,640
-So just listen, okay?
-I know.

793
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:50,800
Sorry?

794
00:50:50,880 --> 00:50:52,320
I know exactly
what you've got to tell me.

795
00:50:53,360 --> 00:50:55,600
-You... You do?
-You and Danny are together now.

796
00:50:55,680 --> 00:50:57,360
That's great, that's how it should be.

797
00:50:57,440 --> 00:51:00,920
But the old man and the blue box,
that's never gonna fit in.

798
00:51:01,120 --> 00:51:04,160
So no more flying around,
no more lying.

799
00:51:04,240 --> 00:51:06,000
No, that's not exactly...

800
00:51:06,160 --> 00:51:07,920
-It's fine.
-No, it's not fine.

801
00:51:08,560 --> 00:51:11,240
It really isn't fine.

802
00:51:11,400 --> 00:51:13,040
I found Gallifrey!

803
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:17,600
Wow!

804
00:51:18,800 --> 00:51:20,040
Oh, my God!

805
00:51:22,600 --> 00:51:24,120
(RUMBLING)

806
00:51:25,080 --> 00:51:28,440
DOCTOR: I entered the co-ordinates,
Just like she said.

807
00:51:30,120 --> 00:51:32,200
And I found Gallifrey.

808
00:51:45,760 --> 00:51:48,160
For once, she wasn't lying.

809
00:52:23,640 --> 00:52:24,640
(GRUNTING)

810
00:52:46,280 --> 00:52:48,080
So what are you gonna do now?

811
00:52:50,440 --> 00:52:52,200
-Go home.
-Okay.

812
00:52:54,080 --> 00:52:55,760
Gallifrey can be a good place.

813
00:52:56,640 --> 00:52:58,040
I can help make it that.

814
00:52:58,560 --> 00:52:59,920
-What, you?
-Shut up!

815
00:53:00,040 --> 00:53:01,920
(LAUGHING) You won't just steal
the Tardis and run away?

816
00:53:02,240 --> 00:53:04,520
No, not this time. Never again.

817
00:53:08,720 --> 00:53:09,720
Never again.

818
00:53:11,480 --> 00:53:13,920
It's a long commute,
so, you know, I thought,

819
00:53:14,040 --> 00:53:16,200
-with you and Danny...
-Yeah.

820
00:53:16,360 --> 00:53:17,360
Me and Danny.

821
00:53:23,760 --> 00:53:25,760
Me and Danny, we are gonna be fine.

822
00:53:26,360 --> 00:53:28,040
Don't you worry. You go home.

823
00:53:28,920 --> 00:53:31,200
(LAUGHING) Go home.

824
00:53:31,720 --> 00:53:33,640
Go be a king, or something.

825
00:53:34,600 --> 00:53:36,440
Yeah, I might do that.

826
00:53:36,920 --> 00:53:38,400
(CHUCKLES) Or queen, you know. Whatever.

827
00:53:39,440 --> 00:53:41,320
Yeah, queen, that would be good, too.

828
00:53:47,880 --> 00:53:48,880
(SIGHING)

829
00:53:51,080 --> 00:53:53,840
Tell you what. Seeing as it's goodbye,
shall we break a habit?

830
00:53:54,040 --> 00:53:55,440
What, what habit?

831
00:53:57,520 --> 00:53:58,520
Hug?

832
00:53:59,520 --> 00:54:00,520
Why not.

833
00:54:00,960 --> 00:54:02,360
Within reason.

834
00:54:07,120 --> 00:54:08,320
Come on, you're on the clock.

835
00:54:08,520 --> 00:54:10,680
Fair enough. (CLEARS THROAT)

836
00:54:23,280 --> 00:54:25,320
Why don't you like hugging, Doctor?

837
00:54:26,680 --> 00:54:28,160
Never trust a hug.

838
00:54:29,480 --> 00:54:31,720
It's just a way to hide your face.

839
00:54:36,480 --> 00:54:37,600
(SOFTLY) Yeah.

840
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:46,000
Doctor?

841
00:54:47,440 --> 00:54:49,840
Travelling with you
made me feel really special.

842
00:54:53,320 --> 00:54:54,880
Thank you for that.

843
00:54:56,440 --> 00:54:58,800
Thank you for making me feel special.

844
00:54:59,600 --> 00:55:01,320
Thank you, for exactly the same.

845
00:55:15,160 --> 00:55:16,520
(WHOOSHING)

846
00:55:40,000 --> 00:55:41,360
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

847
00:55:41,440 --> 00:55:43,320
MAN: Coo-wee.

848
00:55:43,960 --> 00:55:45,200
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

849
00:55:45,400 --> 00:55:46,680
Hello!

850
00:55:47,720 --> 00:55:50,800
Doctor, you know it can't end like that!

851
00:55:51,160 --> 00:55:52,160
Hmm>

852
00:55:52,440 --> 00:55:54,800
We need to get this sorted and quickly.

853
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:56,560
She's not all right, you know.

854
00:55:56,640 --> 00:55:58,480
And neither are you!

855
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:00,120
-I'm coming in.
-(DOOR OPENS)

856
00:56:00,280 --> 00:56:02,160
Ah! There you are!

857
00:56:02,440 --> 00:56:04,400
I knew I'd get round to you eventually.

858
00:56:04,480 --> 00:56:06,720
Now, stop gawping, and tell me.

859
00:56:08,040 --> 00:56:09,640
What do you want for Christmas?

